do al rapporto dello scultore con Anton Francesco Doni e all'influenza delle due lezioni accademiche di Benedetto Varchi sulle arti, il Memoriale è riletto, anche grazie al ritrovamento di documenti inediti, alla luce della complessa operazione di riordino archivistico e interpolazione documentaria attuata da Baccio il Giovane, riconducibile a prassi scrittorie comuni tra gli eruditi fiorentini del primo Seicento.  aThis study, based on extensive archival research, sheds light on the writings attributed to the sixteenth-century sculptor Baccio Bandinelli (Libro del disegno, Memoriale) and analyses them in their historical and artistic context, while offering a portrait of the erudite activity of Bandinelli's grandson, Baccio the Younger, within the broader framework of early modern genealogical culture in Florence.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by Schweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn Italian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aBandinelli, Baccio. 4aDisegno. 4aItalienische Literatur/16. Jahrhundert. 4aMemoriale. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Italian.2bisacsh  a16th-Century Italian Literature.  aBaccio Bandinelli.  aDisegno.  aMemoriale.2 aSchweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z9783111318264oZDB-23-DSP0 cprintz978311125464740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111256085zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111256085zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111256085/original  aGBV-d